# Icon Placeholders

This directory requires two icon files for the Teams app manifest:

## color.png
- Size: 192x192 pixels
- Format: PNG with transparency support
- Purpose: Full-color app icon for Teams catalog and installation dialogs
- Design: Use Parslee branding with white or transparent background
- Color depth: 24-bit or 32-bit (with alpha channel)

## outline.png
- Size: 32x32 pixels
- Format: PNG with transparency support
- Purpose: Monochrome outline icon for Teams left rail and tab headers
- Design: Single-color silhouette (white or black) with transparent background
- Requirements: High-contrast for visibility in both light and dark themes

## Creating Icons

### Using Design Tools
- Adobe Illustrator / Photoshop
- Figma / Sketch
- Canva (free tier supports custom dimensions)

### Online Icon Generators
- https://www.favicon-generator.org/ (supports custom sizes)
- https://realfavicongenerator.net/

### Command-line Tools
```bash
# Resize existing logo to 192x192 (requires ImageMagick)
convert logo.png -resize 192x192 color.png

# Create outline version at 32x32
convert logo.png -resize 32x32 -threshold 50% -negate outline.png
```

## Validation

After creating icons:

1. Verify dimensions:
```bash
file color.png outline.png
# Expected output:
# color.png: PNG image data, 192 x 192, ...
# outline.png: PNG image data, 32 x 32, ...
```

2. Check file size:
```bash
ls -lh *.png
# Recommended: color.png < 50KB, outline.png < 10KB
```

3. Package and validate:
```bash
zip -r ../parslee-dashboard.zip manifest.json color.png outline.png
# Teams Admin Center will validate icons during upload
```

## References
- [Teams App Icons Guidelines](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/platform/concepts/build-and-test/apps-package#app-icons)
